                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <head>693. Telegram 135 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d693fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–856. Confidential; Niact; Limit
                        Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>;
                        cleared by Phleger and <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>
                        and in substance by Sebald. The time of transmission is illegible.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-08-08">August 8, 1956</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d693-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d693-1"/>
                <p>135. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>You will note clear implication in Department’s press release (Deptel 134)
                        that Americans would be allowed travel Communist China once all America
                        prisoners released. Without making this implication explicit, you should
                        exploit it in August 9 meeting so that meaning will be clear to Communists
                        and maximum leverage will be exerted on them to release Americans.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>FYI American Red Cross has agreed to interview Chinese prisoners in US.
                        Communists should not be informed of this at meeting.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
